Citation.sTitle: Excess molar enthalpies of ternary mixtures (1-hexene + tetrahydrofuran + 2,2-dimethylbutane or 2,3-dimethylbutane) at the temperature 298.15 K
Citation.sAbstract: Excess molar enthalpies, measured at the temperature 298.15 K and atmospheric pressure conditions by means of a flow microcalorimeter, are reported for the ternary mixtures x1C6H12 + x2C4H8O + (1 - x1 -  x2) {(CH3)3CCH2CH3 or (CH3)2CHCH(CH3)2}. A smooth representation of the results is described and used to construct constant-enthalpy contours on a Roozeboom diagram. It is shown that good estimates of the excess molar enthalpies of the ternary systems can be obtained from the Liebermann-Fried  model by using the physical properties of the components and the parameters determined from their binary mixtures.
sAuthor: Hasan, S. M. N.[S M Nazmul]
